= BUGS/PROBLEMS/FEATURE REQUESTS

== Race condition: duplicate "verified!" messages

When a user has multiple verified addresses and they all receive Electrum
subscription callbacks at once (e.g., same block), each callback independently
checks conditions and grants access, resulting in multiple "verified!" messages
in the group.

Observed: @kzKallisti verified two addresses, both got activity events
simultaneously, resulted in two "[monitor] Granted access to user X" entries
and two "verified!" messages in the group.

Fix: Check membership status before granting - skip if already authorized.

